The Created vs Resolved gadget does not display the full height of the chart and is unusable when embedded in a Confluence page.  The gadget's iframe has a static 45px height, which I assume means the height value passed in this function is not grabbing the height of the graph:
{code}
gadgets.IfrGadgetService.inherits(gadgets.GadgetService);

gadgets.IfrGadgetService.prototype.setHeight = function(height) {
    if (height > gadgets.container.maxheight_) {
        height = gadgets.container.maxheight_;
    }

    var element = document.getElementById(this.f);
    if (element) {
        element.style.height = height + 'px';
    }
};
{code}

Other gadgets will display normally on the page, such as Agile or Assigned to Me.

Currently when one enters a curly brace in Confluence Rich Text Editor, the character will be treated as a special character for macro opening. This breaks when one uses it in a table like so:

{noformat}
|| Left || Right ||
| { | } |
{noformat}

Produces the following output:

|| Left || Right ||
| { | } |

A customer pointed out that when creating a table in RTE, the behaviour should not be this way:

{quote}
As a user point of view, "Rich Text" is a more UI based editor for user to enter whatever characters including special characters. User would expect to see what they have input without extra formatting or code needed. 

It is different from "Wiki Markup" that offers code based editor allowing user to have more control on the formatting.
{quote}

The work around is to escape the curly braces with an escape character.

{noformat}
|| Left || Right ||
| \{ | \} |
{noformat}

We are using a custom Documentation theme in Confluence 3.2.1_01 (i.e. we are inputting our own configuration rather than using the "out of the box" congiguration). This works well, apart from when we try to add the "Expand All" and "Collapse All" links via the {pagetree} macro. Although the links are displayed, they are pushed too far to the left and half of the "Expand All" link is invisible (see attached screenshot). This has been reproduced on both Firefox 3.6.10 and Internet Explorer 7.

The macro we are using is as follows:

{pagetree:root=Release Notes|expandCollapseAll=true|sort=position|searchBox=true}

We believe it to be a CSS issue.

h4. Workaround 
# Go to Dashboard > Administration > Look and Feel > Custom HTML 
# Copy and paste the following code:
{code}
<style>
.plugin_pagetree_expandcollapse
{
margin-left: 2em;
}
</style>
{code}
# Save the Custom HTML
